Anthrax, Kyrgyzstan
------------
Information received on [and dated] Tue 10 Jul 2018 from Dr Kalysbek Jumakanov, Director Chief State Veterinary Inspector (CVO), State Inspectorate of Veterinary and Phytosanitary Security, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 26 Jun 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 28 Jun 2018
Report date: 10 Jul 2018
Date submitted to OIE: 10 Jul 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 9 Sep 2017
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Bazar-Korgon Rayon, Jany-Akman, Jalal-Abad
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Jun 2018
Outbreak status: resolved (28 Jun 2018)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 62 / 1 / 1 / 0

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 62 / 1 / 1 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.61 percent / 1.61 percent / 100 percent / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: According to the instructions, quarantine-restrictive measures were carried out.

Control measures:
Measures applied:
Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated / Details
Jalal-Abad / Cattle / 70 / Anthrax vaccine
Plus quarantine, disinfection, and no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: no other measures

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak in western Kyrgyzstan can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

